   "message": "The levers holding him back from doing so should be:\n\n- shame & fear of your reaction, how much you might want to see from him to make amends\n- external social pressure, things that he's said and done to justify the past actions & position, knots that he has to now untie. The tighter/deeper this was the more of a barrier this is right now \n- things he feels resentful for that he never told you (that in his mind justify his actions). Typically this would be something he needed from you but never had that courage to ask. Likely because he was intimidated by your competence along specific axes that he lacked in",
